# Database Interactions

All database access must go through Drizzle ORM. Never use raw SQL strings or direct client queries.

## Schema

Tables and relations are defined in `src/db/schema.ts`:
- `decks` — belongs to a `clerkUserId`, has many `cards`
- `cards` — belongs to a `deckId` (cascades on delete)

Always import tables and relations from `@/db/schema`, and the `db` client from `@/db`.

## Querying

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD — Drizzle query with schema
import { db } from "@/db";
import { decks, cards } from "@/db/schema";
import { eq } from "drizzle-orm";

const userDecks = await db.select().from(decks).where(eq(decks.clerkUserId, userId));

// ✅ GOOD — relational query
const deckWithCards = await db.query.decks.findFirst({
  where: eq(decks.id, deckId),
  with: { cards: true },
});

// ❌ BAD — raw SQL
const result = await sql`SELECT * FROM decks WHERE clerk_user_id = ${userId}`;
```

## Mutations

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD
await db.insert(decks).values({ clerkUserId, name, description });
await db.update(decks).set({ name }).where(eq(decks.id, id));
await db.delete(cards).where(eq(cards.id, cardId));
```

## Schema Changes

- All schema changes go in `src/db/schema.ts`
- Run `pnpm db:generate` then `pnpm db:migrate` after schema changes
- Never alter the database directly
